  "texts": [
    "228 Once the public has a solid foundation of knowledge about AI and Constitutional AI, the process can move into the upstream stage of public participation.",
    "In this stage, the public should be actively engaged in generating ideas, proposals, and concerns related to the AI constitution.",
    "This could involve public hearings, online consultations, or other participatory mechanisms that allow a wide range of stakeholders to contribute to the process.",
    "229 The goal of this stage is to ensure that the AI constitution reflects the values, priorities, and concerns of the broader public, thereby enhancing its legitimacy and buy-in.",
    "230 After the public input has been gathered, the process should move into the focused deliberation stage."
  ],
